Since bleaching affects only the visible free and complexed molecules, free binding sites on actin and membrane do not change following bleaching. Furthermore, since the bleached area of the filopodia is extremely small compared to the size of the cell, we can assume that IRSp53free instantly equilibrates after the bleach and its concentration remain unchanged throughout the recovery process. Thus we can simplify the above equations using the following relations:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
